    "mitreControlDescription": "Monitor network data for uncommon data flows that may be related to abuse of [Valid Accounts](https://attack.mitre.org/techniques/T1078) to log into a service specifically designed to accept remote connections, such as RDP, telnet, SSH, and VNC.\n \n Note: Network Analysis frameworks such as Zeek can be used to capture, decode, and alert on network service protocols such as SSH and RDP. #Protocol 6 = TCP #Protocol 17 = UDP\n \n Analytic 1 - Suspicious Protocols\n <code>source=\"*Zeek:*\" AND (port=\"636\" AND protocol=\"6\") OR (port=\"389\" AND protocol=\"17\")</code>",
